paragraphs.text: Lotsa good reasons, but also let’s face it, some folks, both male and female, are simply less ‘ambitious’ than others. Which is another reason why ‘immigrants’ are so important, because they give the whole system an infusion of go-getting energy and initiative, that many of the ‘natives’ have lost.

8dabac401399.title: Guys who feel emasculated by their girlfriends making more money than them probably have bigger…

paragraphs.text: Guys who feel emasculated by their girlfriends making more money than them probably have bigger issues to deal with. Why would you want anything other than your partner making as much money as possible? My girlfriend got a raise recently and now makes more than I do and that is a good thing. What would be even better is if she made ten times as much as I do. Why do people view this as a competition?

paragraphs.text: I make twice what my partner does (but no, I’m not raking it in, he just doesn’t earn a ton). It’s fine for now, but it’s going to cause serious issues with starting a family — I obviously need and want to take time off, but financially that is going to be a big, big stretch given how little his income will cover of our basic expenses.
